cs.MA, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.RO, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on distributed density estimation by a group of anonymous agents. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper discusses applications to social network size estimation. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper presents a theoretical analysis of the algorithm used for density estimation. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is mentioned as an application of the algorithm for density estimation by robot swarms. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is mentioned as an application to random walked-based sampling of sensor networks.
